info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 12 at 6:59AM CDT until further notice by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...Observed flooding changed to Minor severity for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Wisconsin River below Biron Reservoir affecting Wood County. ...FLOOD WARNING FOR SNOWMELT REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Wisconsin River below Biron Reservoir. * WHEN...Until further notice. * IMPACTS...At 1017.0 feet, Widespread wooded lowland flooding. Water approaches a few homes on South Biron Drive in Biron. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 4:10 AM CDT Wednesday the stage was 1017.1 feet. - Forecast...No forecast is available for this location. - Flood stage is 1017.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued this evening.
